                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <strong>1. Initialization & State:</strong> I started by configuring the Terraform Backend to store the state file remotely in an Azure Storage Account container. This ensures that if I run the script from a different machine I'm not overwriting the existing infrastructure which prevents state corruption.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            <strong>2. Resource Definition:</strong> I wrote modular blocks for the Resource Group Virtual Network (VNET) and Subnets. I implemented <code>azurerm_network_security_group</code> resources to define strict inbound/outbound rules allowing only port 22/80/443 and attached them directly to the subnets.
                        </p>
                        <p>
